Proposed Idea: AI Powered Training Data Sanitizer

Core idea
•	6G uses AI models to manage network traffic.
•	These models have to learn from new data constantly to stay accurate as the environment changes.
•	This proposal adds a data sanitizer (whether small ML algo or other) into the O-RAN controller to act as a gatekeeper.
•	Every piece of data sent for training must pass through this sanitizer first.
•	It uses the De-Pois method to compare new data against a small set of known clean samples.
•	If the incoming data looks like a malicious outlier it is dropped before it can reach the primary AI model.

How it stays efficient
•	Checking large files like video or complex radio data would be too slow for 6G.
•	The sanitizer uses extracts smaller bits of data from larger files to quality check data.
•	It only compares these small sections which saves a massive amount of processing power.
•	This allows the filter to protect the network brain without causing huge delays in the connection.

Why it could work
•	It is attack agnostic meaning it stops poisoning even if the specific hack isn’t known.
•	It directly protects the training data which is the biggest weakness in an AI controlled network.

Why it wouldnt work
•	Even a small check adds some latency which might hurt the low latency goals of 6G.
•	If the sanitizer is too strict it might block legitimate data from new types of devices.
•	The system relies on having a perfect set of initial clean data or the whole filter is useless.
•	Smart attackers could try to slowly shift the clean data profile over time to bypass the filter.

